Company Overview of Allianz Asset Management of America L.P.



Snapshot People




Company Overview
Allianz Asset Management of America L.P. is a privately owned investment manager. Through its subsidiaries, the firm primarily provides its services to pension and profit sharing plans. It also caters to high net worth individuals, state and municipal government entities, and charitable organizations. The firm manages separate client-focused equity, fixed income, and balanced portfolios for its clients through its subsidiaries. Through its subsidiaries, it also manages equity, fixed income, and balanced mutual funds for its clients. The firm invests in the public equity and fixed income markets across the globe through its subsidiaries. Through its subsidiaries, it typically invests in growt...
Allianz Asset Management of America L.P. is a privately owned investment manager. Through its subsidiaries, the firm primarily provides its services to pension and profit sharing plans. It also caters to high net worth individuals, state and municipal government entities, and charitable organizations. The firm manages separate client-focused equity, fixed income, and balanced portfolios for its clients through its subsidiaries. Through its subsidiaries, it also manages equity, fixed income, and balanced mutual funds for its clients. The firm invests in the public equity and fixed income markets across the globe through its subsidiaries. Through its subsidiaries, it typically invests in growth, value, and growth oriented value stocks of large-cap, mid-cap, and small-cap companies. The firm was founded in 1990 and is based in Newport Beach, California with an additional office in New York City. Allianz Asset Management of America L.P. operates as a subsidiary of Allianz Asset Management AG.
